usage: git dev [<options>] enter  -- <module-paths>
   or: git dev [<options>] exit   -- <module-paths>
   or: git dev [<options>] finish -- <module-paths>

Manage dev mode.

commands:
    enter                   checkout DEV branches in bundle and specified modules
    exit                    return to PROD mode
                                checkout actual version or next version if --vnext is specified
                                fallback to DEV mode
    finish                  merge DEV branches into PROD branches and return to PROD mode

options:
    -h|--help               display help
    -r|--recursive)         visit specified modules recursively
    --vnext                 return to next version (default to actual version)
    <module-paths>          specific modules to visit (default to current module)
    
example:
    git dev enter                 # enter DEV mode in bundle and current module
    git dev enter                 # enter DEV mode in bundle and current module
    git dev enter -r              # enter DEV mode in bundle and current module recursively
    git dev enter -- m1 m2        # enter DEV mode in bundle and child modules 'm1' and 'm2'
    git dev exit                  # exit DEV mode from current module
    git dev finish                # finish DEV mode in current module
    git dev finish -r -- ../m1    # finish DEV mode in sibling module 'm1' recursively
